so you need to know what a vector is and what a matrix is 

a vector is usually a 1D array 

a matrix is usually a 2D array


shape tells you the dimensions 

axis tells numpy to operate across ! 

so a collection of elements in a 1D array is called , vector components 


what is a vector ?


is a quantity that has both a direction and a size.

so axis in numpy refers to the structural level 

for a 2D array there are two levels ! 

matrix = np.array([
    [10, 20, 30],
    [40, 50, 60],
])


axis 0 → outer level
[
    [10, 20, 30],
    [40, 50, 60]
]


The outer level contains 2 rows.

axis 1 → inner level
[10, 20, 30]

Each inner level contains 3 columns.


remember this !!!

axis=x identifies the dimension, or nesting level, that NumPy operates across and collapses.


